Soft Clip (tanh / tube saturation)                                                                      
  - The Rolling Stones — "Brown Sugar" (cranked Ampeg amp — tubes rounding the peaks naturally)           
  - Led Zeppelin — "Whole Lotta Love" (Supro amp pushed into smooth saturation)                           
  - Stevie Ray Vaughan — "Pride and Joy" (Tube Screamer, which soft-clips with diodes in the feedback loop
   — the classic tanh-like curve)                                                                         
  - Most Motown records have light tape saturation on the mix bus — soft clipping from the magnetic medium

